<paragraph blockId="8.[826,1441,1208,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">
<emphasis box="[826,1064,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Emended diagnosis:</emphasis>
The following character combination is diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[1146,1277,1238,1260]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilango">
<emphasis box="[1146,1277,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">H. chilango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male palpal bulb with slender embolus similar in length to tegulum, 
<collectionCode box="[939,972,1299,1320]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">SA</collectionCode>
ends at embolus base (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1380,1299,1321]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1852,1871]" captionTargetBox="[379,1190,1330,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-97@7.[367,1199,1324,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470, left palpal bulb. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 4A, D</figureCitation>
); VG deep (
<figureCitation box="[894,979,1330,1352]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1852,1871]" captionTargetBox="[379,1190,1330,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-97@7.[367,1199,1324,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470, left palpal bulb. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Embolus strongly curved retrolaterally on distal half (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1143,1360,1382]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1852,1871]" captionTargetBox="[379,1190,1330,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-97@7.[367,1199,1324,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470, left palpal bulb. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 4C, D</figureCitation>
). Pap reduced with one slender spinose seta ventrally that does not exceed the apex of Pap; Rap is narrow with one large spinose seta on dorsal face, the spinose seta exceeds the apex of Rap (
<figureCitation box="[934,1052,1483,1505]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1081,1100]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-0@7.[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. E, labial and maxillary cuspules. F, opisthosoma, lateral view showing urticating setae patch. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, metatarsus I, prolateral view. I, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C, F), 1 mm (E, G–I), 0.5 mm (D)." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 3G, I</figureCitation>
). Metatarsus I almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[834,922,1513,1536]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1081,1100]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-0@7.[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. E, labial and maxillary cuspules. F, opisthosoma, lateral view showing urticating setae patch. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, metatarsus I, prolateral view. I, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C, F), 1 mm (E, G–I), 0.5 mm (D)." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
). Ocular tubercle and eyes normally developed, periocular pigmentation complete (
<figureCitation box="[1306,1429,1544,1566]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1081,1100]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-0@7.[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. E, labial and maxillary cuspules. F, opisthosoma, lateral view showing urticating setae patch. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, metatarsus I, prolateral view. I, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C, F), 1 mm (E, G–I), 0.5 mm (D)." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 3A, D</figureCitation>
). Labial cuspules are highly variable in number, ranging from 16–38 (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1218,1605,1627]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1081,1100]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-0@7.[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. E, labial and maxillary cuspules. F, opisthosoma, lateral view showing urticating setae patch. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, metatarsus I, prolateral view. I, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C, F), 1 mm (E, G–I), 0.5 mm (D)." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 3B, E</figureCitation>
). Urticating setae arranged in two lateral, oval patches, black in colour, with well-defined margins (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1265,1666,1688]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[144,223,1081,1100]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-0@7.[303,1263,195,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Hemirrhagus chilango Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 3470. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. E, labial and maxillary cuspules. F, opisthosoma, lateral view showing urticating setae patch. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, metatarsus I, prolateral view. I, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C, F), 1 mm (E, G–I), 0.5 mm (D)." pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Fig. 3C, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[826,1441,1208,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[851,1113,1697,1718]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilango">
<emphasis box="[851,1113,1697,1718]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Hemirrhagus chilango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from most 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">Hemirrhagus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in having the urticating setae arranged in two lateral patches. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Villafuerte &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2010" box="[1280,1441,1758,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezmilesi">
<emphasis box="[1280,1441,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">H. perezmilesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the tibial apophyses well developed. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendoza Marroquín, 2014" authorityName="Mendoza Marroquín" authorityYear="2014" box="[889,1004,1819,1841]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[889,1004,1819,1841]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="642">H. valdezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1013,1100,1820,1841]" pageId="8" pageNumber="642" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by oval patches of urticating setae with well-defined margins rather than diffuse, and metatarsus I straight rather than curved.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="9" pageNumber="643" startId="9.[144,223,1116,1135]" targetBox="[303,1263,197,1086]" targetPageId="9">
